default2. Feed in Tariffs (FITs)default&#xa0;
default2.1 
defaultUKdefault defaultconstraintsdefault defaulton the financing of FITs aredefault defaultdeeplydefault defaultregressivedefault.default In 2010, the Treasury 'rescued' the FITs 
defaultprogramme
default in the same way that South Africa 'rescued' Nelson Mandela to 
defaultRobben
default Island. It was turned from a self-financing scheme within the energy sector accounts into a fixed-budget 
defaultprogramme
default that had to be counted against public expenditure limits. Since then, the role of DECC has been to 'manage down' expectations within a system that constrains growth and delivers 
defaultorganised
