default4. Simplicitydefault&#xa0;
default4.1 
defaultGermany directs the bulk of its transformation defaultprogrammesdefault through the defaultKfWdefault rather than Energy Utilities. defaultIt also cuts through much of the red tape that constrains UK access to Green Finance.
default&#xa0;
default4.2 
defaultThe defaultKfWdefault simplifies the process of applying for finance and then the trains high street/regional banks (defaultSparkassendefault) to deliver their finance defaultprogrammesdefault.default In 2011, they delivered 5,400 consulting services supporting this delivery mechanism. These covered energy efficiency measures as well as renewable energy investment.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default4.3 
defaultThe German government channels its EU-ETS receipts (approximately default€default1.5bn p.a.) through the defaultKfWdefault in order to de-risk investment in energy and climate work.
default&#xa0;
default4.4 
defaultStandardiseddefault application forms/procedures mean that loan applications are expected to be completed in a single visit to the local bank, once compliance conditions have been metdefault.
default&#xa0;
default4.5 
defaultLoans are normally at the rate of 1%-1.5% and can be for up to 15-20 years.default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
